<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1487,2036]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,277,1487,1513]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Aedeagal preatrium with spine; shaft, lateral view, base short, C-shaped; apex straight, very narrow, spine-like, gonopore medial, dorsal (
<figureCitation box="[727,808,1525,1551]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="62.[151,255,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[249,1353,187,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-126@62.[233,1361,182,1903]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 3 a–t. Pravistylus species. Aedeagus, laterally. a–b, P.lobus sp. n.; c, P. deltoplacussp. n.; d, P. mecophysis sp. n.; e, P. bidentidiscus sp. n.; f, P. brachyplacus sp. n.; g, P. mollidiscus sp. n.; h, P. mecistoplacus sp. n.; i–k, P. mutilidiscus sp. n.; l, P. brachyphysis sp. n.; m, P. odontiophallus sp. n.; n–o, P.eductus (Naudé); p–q, P. exquadratus (Naudé); r, P. tanyoplacus sp. n.; s, P. macropygeus sp. n.; t, P. pollediscus sp. n." pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Figs 3</figureCitation>
aj, 4 ah). Plate medial basal margin lobate, apex sclerotized dorsally, distal medial margin straight, recessed laterad of basal lobe, sclerotized dorsally; lateral margin broadly rounded (
<figureCitation box="[451,521,1600,1626]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="57.[151,255,1711,1735]" captionTargetBox="[198,1389,205,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-63@57.[190,1396,194,1718]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURE 2 a–i. Pravistylus species. Plate, part or whole structure. a, P. varicudiscus sp. n.; b, P. mecistoplacus sp. n.; c, P. digitidiscus sp. n.; d, P. tanyoplacus sp. n.; e–g, P.eductus(Naudé); h–i, P. exquadratus (Naudé)." pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
as). Style distal part far from base (
<figureCitation box="[943,1014,1600,1626]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="66.[151,255,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[198,1391,200,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-128@66.[190,1397,194,1814]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 5 a–p. Pravistylus species. Style, dorsally or ventrally. a–b, P. eductus (Naudé), ventral; c–d, P. exquadratus (Naudé), ventral; e, P. longitrunculus sp. n., ventral; f, P. mecistoplacus sp. n., ventral; g, P. mollidiscus sp. n., dorsal; h, P. scolopygeus sp. n., dorsal; i, P. serratus sp. n., dorsal; j, P. trunculidiscus sp. n., dorsal; k, P. bidentidiscus sp. n., dorsal; l, P. brachyphysis sp. n., dorsal; m, P. brachyplacus sp. n., dorsal; n, P. deltoplacus sp. n., ventral; o–p, P. dentidiscus sp. n., ventral." pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
ab); dorsal apophysis visible below plate (
<figureCitation box="[225,297,1637,1663]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="57.[151,255,1711,1735]" captionTargetBox="[198,1389,205,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-63@57.[190,1396,194,1718]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURE 2 a–i. Pravistylus species. Plate, part or whole structure. a, P. varicudiscus sp. n.; b, P. mecistoplacus sp. n.; c, P. digitidiscus sp. n.; d, P. tanyoplacus sp. n.; e–g, P.eductus(Naudé); h–i, P. exquadratus (Naudé)." pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
as). Female sternite 7 base rectangular, posterior margin with two paired, delicate processes on either side of medial, shallow notch (
<figureCitation box="[584,659,1674,1700]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="70.[151,255,1894,1918]" captionTargetBox="[228,1356,197,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-105@70.[225,1359,194,1900]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="FIGURE 7 a–af. Pravistylus species. Sternite 7 of female, whole structure, or posterior margin. a–b, P. bidentidiscus sp. n.; c, P. brachyphysis sp. n.; d, P. brachyplacus sp. n.; e–f, P. caenophallus sp. n.; g–i, P. deltoplacus sp. n.; j–l, P. dentidiscus sp. n.; m–n, P. digitidiscus sp. n.; o–t, P. eductus (Naudé); u–w, P. exquadratus (Naudé); x–aa, P. indistinctidiscus sp. n.; ab–af, P. interdiscus sp. n." pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Figs 7</figureCitation>
bu &amp; bv).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1487,2036]" box="[196,1309,1711,1738]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,329,1711,1737]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Etymology</emphasis>
. Greek, for the pointed process (
<emphasis box="[715,788,1712,1737]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">skolos</emphasis>
) on the preatrium of the aedeagus (
<emphasis box="[1205,1291,1712,1737]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">phallus</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1487,2036]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,409,1749,1775]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Male and female</emphasis>
. Pale ochraceous; paired, brown longitudinal band on vertex; apex of band on vertex darkened; 3 pairs on pronotum. All cells of tegmina with light brown lining. Hind wing triangular, about one quarter as long as tegmina (
<figureCitation box="[474,543,1824,1850]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="73.[151,255,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[213,1373,194,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-70@73.[213,1373,194,1912]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURE 8 a–h. Pravistylus species. Habitus. a–b, P. bidentidiscus sp. n., a, male; b, female; c–d, P. brachyplacus sp. n., c, male; d, female; e, P. caenophallus sp. n., male; f–g, P. deltoplacus sp. n., male; h, P. dentidiscus sp. n., male." pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
be).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1487,2036]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,259,1861,1887]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[274,419,1861,1887]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Dimensions</emphasis>
. (n = 3) 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[519,608,1861,1887]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Length</emphasis>
: apex of vertex to apex of tegmina 
<quantity box="[1022,1166,1861,1887]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.4">2.4–2.6 mm</quantity>
; apex of vertex to apex of abdomen 
<quantity box="[303,451,1898,1924]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" unit="mm" value="2.75" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.7">2.7–2.8 mm</quantity>
; vertex medially 
<quantity box="[662,811,1898,1924]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" unit="mm" value="0.45" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.5 mm</quantity>
; vertex next to eye 
<quantity box="[1050,1146,1898,1924]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
; pronotum medially 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[211,290,1935,1961]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Width</emphasis>
: head 
<quantity box="[368,461,1936,1962]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
; pronotum 
<quantity box="[594,688,1936,1962]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
. Ocellar diameter 21.6–29.7 µm; ocellocular distance 70.0 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1487,2036]" lastBlockId="43.[151,1436,152,1186]" lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,394,1973,1999]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Genital capsule</emphasis>
. Pygofer, in lateral view, with ventral, dorsal posterior margins broadly rounded; lobe absent (
<figureCitation box="[248,322,2010,2036]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="54.[151,258,1750,1774]" captionTargetBox="[187,1403,201,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-85@54.[180,1407,197,1753]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 1 a–l. Pravistylus species. Pygofer, laterally. a, P. bidentidiscus sp. n.; b, P. brachyphysis sp. n.; c, P. brachyplacus sp. n.; d, P. caenophallus sp. n.; e, P. deltoplacus sp. n.; f–g, P. dentidiscus sp. n.; h, P. digitidiscus sp. n.; i–k, P.eductus(Naudé); l, P. exquadratus (Naudé)." pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
ae). Plate medial basal margin lobate, sclerotized dorsally, distal medial margin straight, recessed laterad of basal lobe, sclerotized dorsally; lateral margin broadly rounded; 5–7 uniseriate macrosetae (
<figureCitation box="[160,233,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="57.[151,255,1711,1735]" captionTargetBox="[198,1389,205,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-63@57.[190,1396,194,1718]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURE 2 a–i. Pravistylus species. Plate, part or whole structure. a, P. varicudiscus sp. n.; b, P. mecistoplacus sp. n.; c, P. digitidiscus sp. n.; d, P. tanyoplacus sp. n.; e–g, P.eductus(Naudé); h–i, P. exquadratus (Naudé)." pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
as); plate 0.8–1.0 times as long as wide. Aedeagus, in lateral view, with shaft arising basally from atrium; preatrium produced into narrow spine; shaft base C-shaped, tapering towards apex; apical half narrow, straight, spine-like, narrower diameter than base of shaft; gonopore dorsomedial, at junction between spine and curved shaft base (
<figureCitation box="[427,504,301,327]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="62.[151,255,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[249,1353,187,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-126@62.[233,1361,182,1903]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 3 a–t. Pravistylus species. Aedeagus, laterally. a–b, P.lobus sp. n.; c, P. deltoplacussp. n.; d, P. mecophysis sp. n.; e, P. bidentidiscus sp. n.; f, P. brachyplacus sp. n.; g, P. mollidiscus sp. n.; h, P. mecistoplacus sp. n.; i–k, P. mutilidiscus sp. n.; l, P. brachyphysis sp. n.; m, P. odontiophallus sp. n.; n–o, P.eductus (Naudé); p–q, P. exquadratus (Naudé); r, P. tanyoplacus sp. n.; s, P. macropygeus sp. n.; t, P. pollediscus sp. n." pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Figs 3</figureCitation>
aj, 4 ah). Style distal part far from anterior medial lobe; apophysis uniformly tapering to narrow point; preapical lobe acute; apophysis protruding medially beyond margin of plate (
<figureCitation box="[1365,1436,338,364]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="66.[151,255,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[198,1391,200,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-128@66.[190,1397,194,1814]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 5 a–p. Pravistylus species. Style, dorsally or ventrally. a–b, P. eductus (Naudé), ventral; c–d, P. exquadratus (Naudé), ventral; e, P. longitrunculus sp. n., ventral; f, P. mecistoplacus sp. n., ventral; g, P. mollidiscus sp. n., dorsal; h, P. scolopygeus sp. n., dorsal; i, P. serratus sp. n., dorsal; j, P. trunculidiscus sp. n., dorsal; k, P. bidentidiscus sp. n., dorsal; l, P. brachyphysis sp. n., dorsal; m, P. brachyplacus sp. n., dorsal; n, P. deltoplacus sp. n., ventral; o–p, P. dentidiscus sp. n., ventral." pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
ab). Connective stem, arms of about similar length and width (
<figureCitation box="[883,953,376,402]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="69.[151,256,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[266,1320,198,1706]" captionTargetId="figure-273@69.[264,1329,194,1706]" captionTargetPageId="69" captionText="FIGURE 6 a–ai. Pravistylus species. Connective, dorsally or ventrally and laterally. a, P. lobus sp. n., ventral; b, P. deltoplacus sp. n., dorsal; c, P. mecophysis sp. n., dorsal; d, P. bidentidiscus sp. n., dorsal; e, P. brachyplacus sp. n., dorsal; f, P. mollidiscus sp. n., dorsal; g, P. mecistoplacus sp. n., dorsal; h, P. mutilidiscus sp. n., dorsal; i, P. brachyphysis sp. n., ventral; j, P. odontiophallus sp. n., dorsal; k, P. odontiophallus sp. n., ventral; l, P.eductus(Naudé), dorsal; m, P. eductus (Naudé), lateral; n–o, P. exquadratus (Naudé), dorsal; p, P. exquadratus (Naudé), lateral; q, P. tanyoplacus sp. n., dorsal; r, P. macropygeus sp. n., dorsal; s–u, P. pollediscus sp. n., dorsal; v, P. scolopygeus sp. n., dorsal; w, P. dentidiscus sp. n., dorsal; x, P. micropygeus sp. n., dorsal; y, P. trunculidiscus sp. n., dorsal; z, P. longitrunculus sp. n., dorsal; aa, P. digitidiscus sp. n., dorsal; ab, P. serratus sp. n., dorsal; ac, P. indistinctidiscus sp. n., dorsal; ad, P. odontopygeus sp. n., dorsal; ae, P. varicudiscus sp. n., ventral; af, P. pelorophallus sp. n., ventral; ag, P. pelorophallus sp. n., lateral; ah, P. scolophallus sp. n., ventral; ai, P. caenophallus sp. n., ventral." pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
ah).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1436,152,1186]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,288,413,439]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Female</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[303,449,413,439]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Dimensions</emphasis>
. (n = 3) 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[556,646,413,439]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Length</emphasis>
: apex of vertex to apex of tegmina 
<quantity box="[1074,1221,413,439]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="2.7" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.6">2.6–2.8 mm</quantity>
; apex of vertex to apex of abdomen 
<quantity box="[366,513,450,476]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3499999999999996" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="3.3499999999999996" valueMax="3.4" valueMin="3.3">3.3–3.4 mm</quantity>
; vertex medially 
<quantity box="[722,817,450,476]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
; vertex next to eye 
<quantity box="[1054,1149,450,476]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
; pronotum medially 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[212,291,487,513]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Width</emphasis>
: head 
<quantity box="[370,515,488,514]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="0.85" valueMax="0.9" valueMin="0.8">0.8–0.9 mm</quantity>
; pronotum 
<quantity box="[650,744,488,514]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
